This exercise from Jen Widerstrom will tone your legs and core as well as improve your balance!

Workout how-to:
Lie faceup on a bench with a resistance band wrapped around bottom of bench and handles under arches of feet. Extend legs straight up and keep lower back pressed into the bench (no arching). Bend left leg, lowering foot so your knee creates a 90-degree angle, then straighten. Do 10 reps. Repeat with right leg.

Don't let your legs fold into your stomach. Continue the movement, doing 8 reps per leg, then 6 reps, and so on until reaching 2.

status_message:
Looking for a workout that cinches your waist and keeps your core strong? This exercise from Jillian Michaels challenges your balance and arm strength in addition to tightening up your deep abdominal muscles!

Workout how-to:
Start in a forearm plank, making a long line from the crown of your head to your heels. Make sure your hips aren't drooping to engage the core and take pressure off your lower back. Hold for 10 seconds. Then, slowly roll into a side plank, so your elbow is directly under your shoulder and your feet are stacked on top of each other. Your body should be in a long, diagonal line from crown of the head to heels. Hold 10 seconds. Finally, roll through forearm plank to do a side plank on the other side. Hold for 10 seconds.
link_name: Exercise How-To: Rolling Plank and Ab Hold
